This paper is primarily focused on image denoising using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of wider CNNs with more convolutions to extract more accurate pixel-distribution features, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks to solve low-level vision problems, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach using quantitative and visual evaluations, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
